Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.21,0:01:19.81,Default,,0000,0000,0008,,{\blur3}宇宙:极冻{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.29,0:00:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}上溯至宇宙初始 周遭还只是一片漆黑{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}In the beginning, there was darkness.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.62,0:00:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不知何时 忽地一声巨响{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}And then... Bang!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.69,0:00:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}时间空间以及物质皆由此发端{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Giving birth to an endless expanding existence{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.49,0:00:09.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}此后不断膨胀 延伸 永无止境{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}of time, space, and matter.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.02,0:00:12.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}每一天 新的发现都在不断为我们解开{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Every day, new discoveries are unlocking{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.48,0:00:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}蕴藏于这里的那些神秘莫测{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}the mysterious, the mind-blowing,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.60,0:00:17.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}令人大开眼界 致命的秘密{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}the deadly secrets of a place we call{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.61,0:00:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们称这个地方为"宇宙"{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}the universe.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.51,0:00:23.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}在这个广袤的太空{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Between stars, between galaxies,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.49,0:00:25.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}大多数星体和星系{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}in the vast majority of space,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.97,0:00:30.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}其温度远低于零下450度{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}the temperature reads more than 450 degrees below zero.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.33,0:00:34.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}极度严寒的太空甚至让我们呼吸的空气{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The deep freeze of space would turn even the air you breathe{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.69,0:00:36.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}变为坚冰{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}into nothing more than solid ice.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.52,0:00:39.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}遥远的冰冻世界{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Now far off frozen places{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.98,0:00:42.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}带来了奇异的新奥秘{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}bring strange new mysteries.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.63,0:00:47.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}布莫让星云也叫领结星云 比太空环境寒冷得多{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The Boomerang or Bow Tie nebula is actually colder than the surrounding space.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.34,0:00:50.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}冰冻世界里有生命吗？{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Is there life on frozen worlds?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.28,0:00:53.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}而且 极端低温为什么会导致{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}And why does the ultimate cold{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.32,0:00:55.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}超乎我们认识的物理现象？{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}change physics as we know it?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.89,0:00:59.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我们能让光变慢到自行车那样的速度{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}We can take light and slow it down to the speed of a bicycle.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.92,0:01:05.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}让我们一起去寻找宇宙里最低温的地方{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Join us as we travel in search of the lowest temperatures in the universe{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.83,0:01:08.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}那个极端严寒的世界吧{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and the ultimate deep freeze.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.90,0:01:25.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}要深刻理解宇宙最低温的地方{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}To appreciate the coldest places in our universe,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.61,0:01:28.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}就得了解{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}it's important to remember{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.25,0:01:31.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它们以前炽热到什么程度{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}just how hot all of existence once was.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.63,0:01:40.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}大爆炸剧烈爆发离子和能量{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}We think of the Big Bang as the ultimate hot event...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.94,0:01:44.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}是一个极度高温的过程{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}An excitement of plasma and energy.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.99,0:01:48.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}在宇宙还处在高温的时候{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}When the universe was really hot,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.40,0:01:50.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它并没有真正成形{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}it was really without form.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.09,0:01:53.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}放射物和粒子在高速运动{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}There was just radiation and particles all zooming around,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.05,0:01:54.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}相互转变{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}turning into each other.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.20,0:02:00.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}大爆炸过程极其高温{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The Big Bang was a supremely hot event,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.74,0:02:04.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}大约是一亿兆兆度的开氏温度{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}roughly a hundred million trillion trillion Kelvins.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.55,0:02:10.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}科学家们所说的开氏温度{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Scientists measure temperature using the Kelvin scale,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.20,0:02:13.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}其基准是绝对零度{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}which begins at absolute zero{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.59,0:02:15.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}那是已知的最低温度{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The coldest cold we know{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.05,0:02:18.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}原子运动此时完全不存在{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}A complete lack of atomic movement.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.05,0:02:26.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}在地球上 平均温度是开氏288度{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}On Earth... the average temperature is 288 Kelvins...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.30,0:02:30.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}即华氏59度{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Or 59 degrees Fahrenheit...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.08,0:02:35.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}两种表述虽然不同 但都是指同一温度{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Two different ways of noting the same temperature.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.06,0:02:37.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}宇宙形成之初{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}When our universe first formed,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.78,0:02:41.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}温度很高 甚至原子都不能存在{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}it was so hot that not even atoms could exist.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.44,0:02:44.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}整个宇宙除了单纯的能量 什么都没有{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The entire universe was nothing except for pure energy.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.96,0:02:48.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}在一百秒后{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It took a hundred seconds for our universe{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.33,0:02:51.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}宇宙温度降到了十亿度{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}to cool to the point that it was only a billion degrees.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.16,0:02:55.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}在很长的时间里 温度仍然很高{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}For a long time, everything was so hot{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.26,0:02:58.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}一切都被分裂为亚原子微粒{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}that everything was divided into subatomic particles{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.35,0:03:01.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}不是现在传统的原子状态{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Not real traditional atoms the way that we think of matter now.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.77,0:03:05.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}当宇宙温度降至足够低{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The universe had to cool down to a sufficiently low temperature{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.67,0:03:08.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}首先是原子核得以形成{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}that, first of all,atomic nuclei could form,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.46,0:03:10.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}然后中性原子形成{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and then neutral atoms could form.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.85,0:03:14.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}因此 如果不是宇宙温度降到足够低{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}So without the universe cooling down to a sufficiently low temperature,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.14,0:03:16.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我们就不会存在{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}we wouldn't exist.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.02,0:03:23.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}宇宙温度继续下降 直到大爆炸后的56 000年{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The universe kept cooling, until 56,000 years after the big bang{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.19,0:03:25.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它冷却至9 000度{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}it had cooled to 9,000 degrees.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.78,0:03:32.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}在大爆炸380 000年后 则下降至{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}And the universe kept cooling, until 380,000 years after the Big Bang{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.67,0:03:34.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}大约开氏3 000度{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}temperatures reached about 3,000 Kelvin.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.26,0:03:39.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}这是一个拐点 物质与能量终于分开{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}And that was the point out which matter and energy finally parted company.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.58,0:03:44.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}正是温度的下降 才让我们能够开始理解{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}As temperatures dropped to a level we can start to comprehend{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.17,0:03:48.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}热量与温度之间的关系{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It's important to understand the relationship between heat and temperature.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.17,0:03:52.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}热量是能量转移的量度{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Heat is a measurement of energy transfer.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.91,0:03:55.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}温度是作用力{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Temperature is action.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.03,0:03:59.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}让微粒持续碰撞{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}One of the easiest ways to think of temperature{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.27,0:04:01.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}是观察温度最简单的方法之一{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}is as the constant collision of particles.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.38,0:04:04.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}你增加房间里气体的量{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}You increase the amount of gas in a room,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.84,0:04:07.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它们会开始碰撞--互相紧挨着{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}they start colliding... One particle against another...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.67,0:04:12.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}就象下午人流高峰期的东京街头{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Like people in a busy crosswalk on a Tokyo rush-hour afternoon.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.64,0:04:17.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}正如这些气体分子相互碰撞 温度会升高一样{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}As those gas molecules collide one with another, the temperature goes up.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.96,0:04:20.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}在人碰人时{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}And as those people collide one with another,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.67,0:04:24.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}速度被转移 人会趔趄{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}their velocities get transferred, people get bumped forward,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.60,0:04:26.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}体温也会升高{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}their temperature goes up.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.73,0:04:28.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}如果人少了{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Now you start removing people...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.16,0:04:31.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}碰撞会变得不频繁{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Those collisions, they become less frequent.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.09,0:04:35.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}神经变得不紧张 体温就会下降{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Nerves become less frayed... The temperature drops.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.21,0:04:39.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}同样地 当你抽走房间里的气体{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}And in the same way, as you remove gas from a room,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.44,0:04:44.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}碰撞变得不频繁 气体温度就会降下来{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}the collisions become less frequent, and it becomes cooler to experience.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.05,0:04:52.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}人类在建设家园的时候{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}As mankind has spread out over all the lands that make up our home in the universe,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.66,0:04:57.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}领略到了极寒地区的独特魅力{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}areas of extreme cold hold a special fascination.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.49,0:05:00.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}在地球上测到的最低温度{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The coldest temperature ever measured on Earth{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.63,0:05:02.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}是在南极洲{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}was measured in Antarctica,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.32,0:05:05.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它超过了零下125度{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}at over 125 degrees below zero.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.49,0:05:09.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}这杯饮料里的干冰{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Dry ice, like the ice in this drink,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.98,0:05:13.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}大约是在零下109度时凝结的{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}freezes out at about 109 degrees below zero.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.41,0:05:18.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}所以在南极洲 你能找到自然形成的干冰{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}So you could have naturally occurring dry ice in the conditions found in Antarctica,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.11,0:05:19.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}因为那里非常冷{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}it's so cold.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.16,0:05:24.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}在见识了我们星球最低温的地方后{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Having found the coldest place on our planet,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.55,0:05:28.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我们现在去探寻太阳系最低温的地方{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}we now journey to the coldest place in our Solar System.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.43,0:05:32.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}出乎意料的是 我们并不需要去很远{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}And surprisingly, we don't have to go very far.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.21,0:05:36.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}事实上 人类曾到过那里{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}In fact, it's a place where humans have already been.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.56,0:05:39.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}从已知情况来看 最冷的地方{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}From what we know today, the coldest place{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.06,0:05:41.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}出乎人们的预料{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}isn't exactly where you'd expect it.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.52,0:05:44.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}月球轨道探测器{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The Lunar Reconnaissance Orbiter{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.99,0:05:49.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}在阳光永远照不到的地方{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}has detected a temperature of minus 397 degrees fahrenheit{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.74,0:05:53.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}发现其中一处只有华氏-397度{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}in one of those places where the sun's light never quite reaches.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.85,0:05:59.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它就位于月球一座环形山的底部{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It's actually in the bottom of a crater of our Earth's own Moon.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.14,0:06:03.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}当月球环绕地球时 它缓慢地自转{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}As the Moon goes around the Earth, it slowly rotates.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.93,0:06:08.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}实际上 每绕地球一次就恰好自转一周{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}In fact, it rotates exactly once per time around the planet,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.53,0:06:11.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}所以我们总是看到月球的同一个面{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}allowing us to always see the same face of the Moon.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.96,0:06:14.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}在环绕的时候{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}But as it goes around,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.66,0:06:18.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}阳光永远不能从北极下落{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}sunlight is never able to reach down into the northern pole{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.17,0:06:20.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}或是从南极升起{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}or reach up into the southern pole.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.06,0:06:25.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}两地的环形山会永恒地呆在阴影里{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}And craters in those two regions are able to stay in constant shadow{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.25,0:06:29.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}因为阳光仅从其边缘一掠而过{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}because the sunlight simply glances past the edge of the crater,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.48,0:06:31.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}永远都不会照射进去{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}but never actually shines inside.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.13,0:06:37.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}科学家在月球上发现极度严寒的现象后{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Once scientists discovered the ultra-deep freeze on our own Moon,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.85,0:06:40.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}他们意识到 另有一个地方{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}they realized there was another place{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.86,0:06:44.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}即使位于如火的行星 也会同样寒冷{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}that could be equally cold... On a planet of fire.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.28,0:06:48.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}就象月球的那些环形山{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The realization that craters{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.27,0:06:50.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它们会保护冰远离阳光{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}like those on the Moon could protect ices from sunlight,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.00,0:06:53.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我们认识到{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}made us start to realize that{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.02,0:06:57.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}在任何地方的环形山 几乎都可能找到冰{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}it's possible to find ices in craters almost anywhere.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.61,0:06:59.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}水星是最靠近太阳的行星{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Mercury is the closest planet to the Sun.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.31,0:07:02.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}在向阳面 极为高温{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}And its sunlit side is incredibly hot{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.02,0:07:05.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}温度在零上数百度以上{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Many hundred of degrees above absolute zero.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.02,0:07:09.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}但水星的某些部分却是永恒地寒冷{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}But there's some parts of Mercury that are perpetually cold{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.71,0:07:12.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}几乎是太阳系最冷的地方{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Among the coldest places in the Solar System.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.65,0:07:17.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}水星的倾斜{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It's Mercury's tilt... Or lack thereof...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.63,0:07:20.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}保持了两极上环形山的严寒{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Which keeps its polar craters in a deep freeze.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.02,0:07:24.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}行星的倾斜以倾斜度来衡量{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The tilt of the planet is called its obliquity.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.65,0:07:27.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}地球大约倾斜23.5度{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Earth is tilted about 23 1/2 degrees.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.46,0:07:31.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}所以我们的两极每年只有六个月见到阳光{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}So our poles see sunlight about six months out of the year.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.31,0:07:34.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}水星的倾斜度几乎为零{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}On Mercury the obliquity is almost zero.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.52,0:07:36.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}极地上某些深邃的环形山{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}So at some deep craters at the poles,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.75,0:07:40.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}会有永久阴影 终年不见阳光{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}there are spots that are permanently shadowed and never see sunlight.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.88,0:07:45.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}虽然在太阳系里 离太阳越远就会越冷{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Although the Solar System gets colder the further you travel from the Sun,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.40,0:07:49.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}但外层行星和它们卫星的寒冷{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}the icy conditions of the outer planets and moons{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.50,0:07:52.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}并不能排除生命存在的可能{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}do not rule out the possibility of life.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.25,0:07:55.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}在太阳系外边缘{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Out in the outer edges of our Solar System,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.15,0:08:00.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}有各种各样的冰冻卫星{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}we see a whole variety of frozen moons orbiting the outer planets.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.95,0:08:05.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}在木星 土星 天王星和海王星周围{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Around Jupiter, Saturn, Uranus and Neptune{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.87,0:08:08.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}全都是冰冻小世界{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}are all of these little frozen worlds.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.89,0:08:11.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}令人吃惊的是 可能 仅仅是可能{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}And what's amazing is maybe, just maybe,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.29,0:08:14.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}有一些能支持生命存在{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}some of them can support life.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.05,0:08:18.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}科学家已经证实{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Scientists have overwhelming evidence{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.54,0:08:21.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}木星的卫星木卫二{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}to support the notion that on Jupiter's moon Europa{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.26,0:08:26.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}在其表面冰层下 存在着一个流动的海洋{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}there is an icy crust overlying a liquid ocean underneath.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.32,0:08:30.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}太空生物学公认{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}A common tenet of astrobiology{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.47,0:08:33.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}有液态水 生命就有可能{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Where there is liquid water there's the chance for life.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.51,0:08:39.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}科学家们迫切希望象冰海渔夫一样{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Scientists desperately want like ice fishermen{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.61,0:08:44.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}能到冰面上去挖洞 看看能捕捉到什么样的生命{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}to go and dig a hole in the ice and see what life we can pull up.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.37,0:08:50.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}因为它会深藏于木卫二的海洋深处{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}'Cause it could be that deep in the heart of those oceans of Europa,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.90,0:08:53.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}就好比地球的海洋深处{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}just like deep in the heart of the Earth's oceans,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.82,0:08:56.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}那里的火山不仅养育细菌{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}there's volcanoes that support not just bacteria{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.01,0:09:00.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}还养育着全体生命群--海藻 海黄瓜{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}but entire colonies of life Seaweed, sea cucumbers.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.30,0:09:05.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我们所知道的生命 是能够在木卫二海洋存在的{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Life as we know it could exist in the oceans of Europa.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.95,0:09:10.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}土星有一个卫星 它比较活跃{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}One of Saturn's moons is a bit more active,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.05,0:09:14.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}不断地向太空喷射冰雪{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}blasting snow out into space.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.20,0:09:18.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}土星的恩克拉多斯卫星有冰喷泉{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Saturn's moon Enceladus has ice geysers.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.15,0:09:22.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}科学家们在研究这些冰喷泉的时候{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}And scientists, in trying to find a mechanism for these geysers,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.66,0:09:26.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}并没有在其中发现液态水{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}can find no good mechanism that doesn't involve liquid water.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.46,0:09:32.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}木卫二间歇泉喷发的冰{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Ice from the erupting geysers on Enceladus{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.12,0:09:35.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}覆盖着附近卫星 使之反光得更厉害{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}is coating nearby moons, making them more reflective.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.45,0:09:40.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}科学家们是如何知道这些冰冻之地{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}So how did scientists know that frozen places,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.75,0:09:45.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}例如木卫二和恩克拉多斯 发生地质活动的呢？{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}such as Europa and Enceladus, were geologically active?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.83,0:09:48.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}关键之处就在于它们光滑的表面{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The key lies in their smooth surfaces.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.40,0:09:53.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}通过"航行者"航天器近距离拍摄恩克拉多斯{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}When the Voyager Spacecraft sent back the first up-close images of Saturn's moon Enceladus,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.01,0:09:56.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}他们在广袤的区域里 并没有看到环形山{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}they saw huge regions with no craters.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.43,0:10:00.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}这说明了环形山被覆盖 其外观被改变了{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}This tells us that whatever craters were there were filled in, they were resurfaced.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.60,0:10:04.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}这种现象很活跃--它们正在被覆盖{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It tells us this is an active object... Stuff's going on here.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.97,0:10:08.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}卫星 小行星 行星{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The number of craters on a planetary surface,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.61,0:10:12.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}其环形山的数量 反映了表面形成的时间{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}moon, asteroid, planet, tells us about the age of that surface.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.67,0:10:15.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}在木卫四或者月球的表面{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}On Jupiter's moon Callisto or our own Moon,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.41,0:10:19.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}有许多环形山 这说明其外表面非常古老{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}we see a lot of craters telling us we have a very old surface...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.82,0:10:21.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}正如这里的冰{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Just like this ice here.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.68,0:10:23.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它明显就是旧冰{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}This ice is obviously old ice.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.94,0:10:26.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}有片状的 有雪花状的{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It has cuts, it has snow.{\r}
